p><p>该应用程序是一个围墙花园，不与任何健身跟踪或睡眠跟踪应用程序集成。不过，它确实与<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2016-09-17-pokemon-go-plus-hands-on.html"><ins>Pokémon Go Plus 手环配对，</ins></a>让用户通过按下设备上的按钮即可开始睡眠跟踪。使用这款手链还可以鼓励戴着睡帽的皮卡丘罕见地来访。手环的价格约为 30 美元，即将推出的<em>Pokémon Sleep</em>是一款免费应用程序。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/pokemon-sleep-is-coming-later-this-month-and-theres-a-gameplay-trailer-to-prove-it-182444048.html ?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/pokemon-sleep-is-coming-later-this-month-and-theres-a-gameplay-trailer-to-prove-it-182444048.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 53d1adb6-7fda-4ba8-929e-5e5bfa059ae7</guid><dc:creator>劳伦斯·邦克</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Thu, 06 Jul 2023 18:24:44 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1688667885</ingested><modified> 2023-07-06T18:24:49+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Lawrence Bonk]]></category><media:content height="327" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/3e1bac40-1c26-11ee-bf7f-85da1b16a49d" width="578"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="327" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/3e1bac40-1c26-11ee-bf7f-85da1b16a49d" width="578"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[The Pokémon Company]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Logo for Pokémon Sleep.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Pokémon Sleep]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[The US is destroying the world's last known chemical weapons stockpile]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>世界上所有政府都将（至少在官方上）退出化学武器业务。美国陆军<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2023/07/06/us/chemical-weapons-stockpile.html">告诉</a><em>《纽约时报》，</em>最快将于明天 7 月 7 日销毁世界上最后一批已申报的化学武器库存。美国和大多数其他国家同意在 1997 年《化学武器公约》生效后 10 年内彻底消除其武库，但美国收藏的规模之大（许多弹头已有几十年的历史）以及安全处置的复杂性仍然存在国家迟到了。</p><p>目前的方法依靠机器人对充满化学物质的炮弹和火箭进行刺穿、排水和清洗，然后将其烘烤以使其无害。排出的气体在热水中稀释，并用细菌（芥子气）或苛性钠（神经毒剂） <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2015-03-18-chemical-weapons-destroyed-metal-compound.html">中和</a>。然后将剩余的液体焚烧。团队在销毁开始前使用 X 射线检查是否有泄漏，并远程监控机器人以尽量减少与危险材料的接触。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>陆军最初希望通过将这些武器沉没在船上来处理它们，就像之前悄悄做的那样，但由于潜在的环境影响而面临公众的强烈反对。 20 世纪 80 年代焚烧化学制剂的提议也遭到了反对，尽管军方最终以这种方式销毁了大部分库存。</p><p>美国最后一次使用化学武器是在第一次世界大战中，但几十年来一直生产化学武器作为威慑。对该计划的关注首次在 1968 年激增，当时羊群的奇怪死亡事件导致人们发现陆军在美国各地储存化学武器，甚至进行露天测试。</p><p>这项措施只会消除已确认的库存。尽管俄罗斯坚称其在 2017 年销毁了最后的化学武器，但仍被<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2018/03/20/world/europe/russia-chemical-weapons-novichok.html">指控</a>秘密制造神经毒气。亲政府的叙利亚军队和 ISIS 极端分子在 2010 年代的大部分时间里都在使用这些武器。这并不能阻止敌对国家和恐怖分子使用毒素。</p><p>即便如此，这仍然是一个重要的里程碑。除了消灭一整类大规模杀伤性武器之外，它还代表着减少战争杀伤力的又一步。 <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/spacex-objects-to-ukraine-starlink-drones-215629197.html">无人机</a>减少了操作员（尽管不是目标）的暴露，人工智能研究员杰弗里·辛顿（Geoffrey Hinton）等专家设想了一个<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/ai-pioneer-geoffrey-hinton-isnt-convinced-good-ai-will-triumph-over-bad-ai-181536702.html">机器人互相争斗的</a>时代。虽然人类理想上会完全结束战争，但这样的努力至少可以减少伤亡。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/the-us-is-destroying-the-worlds-last-known-chemical-weapons-stockpile-181026211.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/the-us-is-destroying-the-worlds-last-known-chemical-weapons-stockpile-181026211.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 404fc787-b17f-4fb0-9c92-2f29dc4d4f88</guid><dc:creator>乔恩·芬加斯</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Thu, 06 Jul 2023 18:10:26 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1688667027</ingested><modified> 2023-07-06T18:10:32+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Politics & Government]]></category><category><![CDATA[Military & Defense]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Jon Fingas]]></category><media:content height="1651" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/096bd5d0-1c1f-11ee-8276-e1ca0a8ed300" width="2200"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1651" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/096bd5d0-1c1f-11ee-8276-e1ca0a8ed300" width="2200"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Handout . / reuters]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Mustard gas-filled 155mm projectiles are seen inside a chemical storage igloo, at the Pueblo Chemical Depot in an undated photo provided by the U.S. Army Chemical Materials Activity (CMA) in Pueblo, Colorado. The destruction of 2,600 tons of World War Two-era mustard agent weapons banned by international treaty began on March 18, 2015 at a U.S. Army depot in southern Colorado, officials said. REUTERS/U.S. Army Chemical Materials Activity/handout via Reuters  (UNITED STATES - Tags: MILITARY SCIENCE TECHNOLOGY)]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[USA-MUSTARDGAS]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[The best Android phones for 2023]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>与苹果是唯一的 iOS 生态系统不同，Android 手机市场的最大优点之一是有多种不同的设备和制造商可供选择。也就是说，当真正需要升级时，丰富的选择可能会让您选择合适的手机变得更加困难。如果您正在寻找一部新手机，但不知道从哪里开始，我们会为您精选适合各种预算的最佳 Android 手机。</p><h2>购买新的 Android 手机需要注意什么</h2><h3>表现</h3><p>当谈到挑选我们最喜欢的 Android 手机时，我们寻找的主要因素非常简单：良好的性能（计算和人工智能）、漂亮的显示屏、坚固的设计、锋利的相机、长电池寿命以及对持续软件支持的重大承诺。对于性能，我们不仅会查看基准测试和其他指标，还会根据响应能力来评估手机。无论您是在阅读、浏览社交媒体还是玩游戏，没有人想要一台感觉迟缓的设备。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><h3>展示</h3><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-02/54f98de0-a87e-11ed-afd1-54c1e8d571fc" alt="虽然规格与去年相比没有太大变化，但三星 Galaxy S23 Ultra 的 6.8 英寸 120Hz AMOLED 显示屏仍然是市场上最好的智能手机屏幕之一。" data-uuid="f90b4b62-0619-3c10-8a7b-abccc2d7e842"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">萨姆·卢瑟福/Engadget</div></figure><p>在显示器方面，我们通常更喜欢能够产生丰富、饱和的色彩且亮度至少为 600 尼特的 OLED 面板，尽管我们的许多顶级中端和高端手机的亮度都可以达到 1,000 尼特或更高。最近，我们最喜欢的大多数设备还支持 90Hz 或 120Hz 快速刷新率的屏幕，这增加了额外的平滑度和流动性。</p><h3>设计</h3><p>现在我们承认，在决定哪些手机看起来最好时存在一些主观性，但还有其他设计方面，例如防尘防水或屏幕耐用性，可以对长期生存产生很大影响。考虑对无线充电、电源共享（又称反向无线充电）和 UWB 连接的支持等因素也很重要，这些因素可能会影响手机与其他设备的交互方式。</p><h3>相机</h3><p>显然，对于照片，我们希望在明亮和弱光条件下拍摄清晰、色彩丰富的照片。我们希望视频剪辑具有高动态范围、丰富的音频和流畅的图像稳定性。用于超广角和长焦镜头的额外相机是一个优点。考虑专用夜间模式、支持各种视频录制分辨率以及延时摄影、慢动作等其他照片模式等功能也很重要。</p><h3>电池和软件</h3><p>最后，在电池续航时间方面，我们希望设备能够拥有全天的续航时间，并且在我们的本地视频运行测试中也能取得出色的成绩（一次充电至少 16 小时，但显然越多越好）。在过去的几年里，无线充电功能几乎无处不在，我们的大多数首选产品都具有这种额外的功能。最后，随着人们使用手机的时间比以往任何时候都长，我们希望看到公司承诺至少三年的软件支持、升级和定期安全更新。</p><h2>最好的安卓手机</h2><h2></h2><h2>最佳 Android 手机：Google Pixel 7 Pro</h2><p><core-commerce id="6c0fc07b5bfe47688db2b2d8968dd3ac" data-type="product-list"></p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9Hb29nbGUtUGl4ZWwtUHJvLVNtYXJ0cGhvbmUtVGVsZXBob3RvL2RwL0IwQkNRV1lSMlo_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8tbnotMjAiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjhkZTg5YTJkLWIzNDQtNGQyMi1hZTg5LWIzMTRiNzVmY2IxZCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAZuzv_OntlWKtc3kU_R6DzOAL7wpXaS2FC4opPdWgj1c&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FGoogle-Pixel-Pro-Smartphone-Telephoto%2Fdp%2FB0BCQWYR2Z">Pixel 7 Pro</a>和标准<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9Hb29nbGUtUGl4ZWwtNy01Ry1BbmRyb2lkLVBob25lL2RwL0IwQkNRWFk1Mlo_dGg9MSZ0YWc9Z2RndDBjLXAtby1uei0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiOGRlODlhMmQtYjM0NC00ZDIyLWFlODktYjMxNGI3NWZjYjFkIn0&amp;signature=AQAAASpA5F4f1KXYW4oQgh_yMRWREBd33uFTYbfquLiIWWVt&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FGoogle-Pixel-7-5G-Android-Phone%2Fdp%2FB0BCQXY52Z%3Fth%3D1">Pixel 7</a>可能不是市场上绝对最快的手机，但它们在纯粹性能方面的不足可以通过周到的软件来弥补。得益于谷歌的 Tensor G2 芯片，Pixel 7 系列具有强大的人工智能和机器学习功能，支持设备上语言识别和实时翻译等功能。您还可以获得华丽的 OLED 显示屏以及当今<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-smartphones-140004900.html">智能手机中最佳的整体相机质量</a>。标准 Pixel 7 的起价仅为 600 美元，谷歌最新旗舰产品的价值也令人难以置信。两者之间的主要区别在于 Pixel 7 Pro 拥有更大的 6.7 英寸屏幕，并配备第三个后置摄像头，支持 ​​5 倍光学变焦。但无论您喜欢更小还是更大的设备，Pixel 7 或 Pixel 7 Pro 都不会出错。</p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/google-pixel-7-and-pixel-7-pro-review-still-the-best-bargain-in-flagship-phones-170031940.html"><strong>阅读我们对 Google Pixel 7 Pro 的完整评论</strong></a></p><h2>最佳中端Android手机：OnePlus 11</h2><p><core-commerce id="1013518286f041b7be4c6a83405b2a98" data-type="product-list"></p><p>对于那些想要一部大屏幕、出色的摄像头和卓越性能的手机，但价格又低于传统旗舰机的人来说， <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9PbmVQbHVzLVVubG9ja2VkLVNtYXJ0cGhvbmUtSGFzc2VsYmxhZC1Qcm9jZXNzb3IvZHAvQjBCTldRQzlGSi8_dGg9MSZ0YWc9Z2RndDBjLXAtby1uei0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiOGRlODlhMmQtYjM0NC00ZDIyLWFlODktYjMxNGI3NWZjYjFkIn0&amp;signature=AQAAAX-H-HDCbozJUO5Ri9Pm3mvkdJEw_ZVvcGSOfpg2-wVG&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FOnePlus-Unlocked-Smartphone-Hasselblad-Processor%2Fdp%2FB0BNWQC9FJ%2F%3Fth%3D1">OnePlus 11</a>在廉价手机和更高端设备之间取得了良好的平衡。在很多方面，OnePlus 11 就像更实惠的<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/samsung-galaxy-s23-review-a-solid-phone-thats-probably-not-worth-the-upgrade-173026346.html">Galaxy S23+</a> 。你不仅拥有类似的 6.7 英寸 120Hz 显示屏，还配备快速的 Snapdragon 8 Gen 2 芯片和 5,000 mAh 的大电池。与此同时，得益于 OnePlus 强劲的 100 瓦有线充电功能，它的充电速度比任何谷歌或三星手机都快。在相机方面，该公司与哈苏的持续合作显着提高了图像质量。</p><p> OP11的主要缺点是其IP64防尘防水等级低于竞争对手的设备，而且相机的2倍光学变焦镜头感觉有点短。但随着 OnePlus 增加了更广泛的运营商兼容性，并承诺四年的操作系统升级和五年的安全补丁，OP11 是一个装备精良的选择，成本明显低于竞争对手。</p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/oneplus-11-review-price-release-date-cameras-150015371.html"><strong>阅读我们对 OnePlus11 的完整评论</strong></a></p><h2>最佳预算 Android 手机：Google Pixel 7a</h2><p><core-commerce id="8af72094077040eea8d5a86a5802492c" data-type="product-list"></p><p>售价 500 美元的<a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3N0b3JlLmdvb2dsZS5jb20vP3BsaT0xJmhsPWVuLVVTIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiI4ZGU4OWEyZC1iMzQ0LTRkMjItYWU4OS1iMzE0Yjc1ZmNiMWQifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAWBJdvYYzyh8qXtdVOgZLQuwiN_d6MKNMXdgavl3iu6b&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fstore.google.com%2F%3Fpli%3D1%26hl%3Den-US">Pixel 7a</a>满足了我们对一款出色、价格实惠的 Android 手机的所有需求。新功能包括更快的 Tensor G2 芯片、更流畅的 90Hz 显示屏，以及首次在 Google A 系列手机上支持无线充电。它采用了 IP67 防水等级的全新设计，外观和触感与标准 Pixel 7 相似，但价格便宜 100 美元。得益于五年的安全更新和至少三年的软件更新，您还可以获得大力支持。 Pixel 7a 唯一的缺点相当小，包括缺乏专用变焦镜头以及不支持 mmWave 5G（除非您从 Verizon 购买稍微贵一点的 550 美元型号）。</p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/google-pixel-7a-review-its-got-everything-you-need-and-more-for-just-499-184517525.html"><strong>阅读我们对 Google Pixel 7a 的完整评论</strong></a></p><h2>最佳优质 Android 手机：三星 Galaxy S23 Ultra</h2><p><core-commerce id="a6ef601583384a64973e928e7c0f3c94" data-type="product-list"></p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAVe1eNCu8XYyFXTbnswQHxk2ZNnTC1JBBPVTrU2LLOhQ&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FSAMSUNG-Factory-Unlocked-Android-Smartphone%2Fdp%2FB0BLP2PY6N%2F%3Fth%3D1">Galaxy S23 Ultra</a>的起价为 1,200 美元，非常昂贵，但它具有出色的性能，几乎拥有您在智能手机中想要或需要的一切。它拥有巨大的<a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/samsung-galaxy-s23-ultra-review-specs-price-photo-and-video-take-center-stage-140034341.html">6.8 英寸 OLED 显示屏</a>，具有 120Hz 自适应刷新率，总共五个摄像头（主摄像头、超广角摄像头、3 倍变焦、10 倍变焦和自拍摄像头）以及内置 S Pen，用于绘图和记事——服用。它还配备了 5,000 mAh 的大电池，可提供我们在任何手机上见过的最长的运行时间。随着三星对软件支持的重新承诺，您可以期待至少四次主要操作系统升级和五年定期安全补丁。</p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:12;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/samsung-galaxy-s23-ultra-review-specs-price-photo-and-video-take-center-stage-140034341.html"><strong>阅读我们对三星 Galaxy S23 Ultra 的完整评论</strong></a></p><h2>最佳可折叠安卓手机：三星 Galaxy Z Fold 4</h2><p><core-commerce id="84dd72504e4c4bb48916779e737f37bb" data-type="product-list"></p><p>虽然<a data-i13n="cpos:13;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/samsung-galaxy-z-flip-4-review-camera-samples-specs-price-battery-life-170027529.html">Galaxy Z Flip 4</a>可以说是市场上最时尚、最紧凑的手机，但更大、更昂贵的<a data-i13n="cpos:14;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9kcC9CMEIzVEJCS1E4Lz90YWc9Z2RndDBjLXAtby1uei0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiOGRlODlhMmQtYjM0NC00ZDIyLWFlODktYjMxNGI3NWZjYjFkIn0&amp;signature=AQAAARGbIenXQIiGuO5-j5ONQNZPqiP9_vwb1KrhyjeDKKgD&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0B3TBBKQ8%2F">Z Fold 4</a>就像三合一设备，这使其成为移动设备中的独角兽。当您只需要回复短信或快速查找地址时，其 6.2 英寸的外盖屏幕让一切变得轻而易举。但当您想坐下来看电影或玩游戏时，您可以打开 Fold，露出令人惊叹的 7.8 英寸柔性显示屏。作为一款可折叠手机，当您需要时它会变得紧凑，而当您不需要时它会在大屏幕上提供身临其境的观看体验。由于支持手写笔输入，您甚至可以使用专为 Fold 设计的三星 S Pen 来快速绘制或记下笔记。最重要的是，Z Fold 4 的 OLED 显示屏非常适合阅读书籍和漫画。与几乎任何其他非三星可折叠产品不同的是，Fold 还具有 IP68 防尘防水等级。从很多方面来说，这个东西都是手机领域的瑞士军刀。当然，它有点笨重，而且 1,800 美元的价格并不是任何人都能负担得起的。但这款三星手机能够根据情况充当手机、平板电脑、电子阅读器等功能，这使得 Z Fold 4 独树一帜。</p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:15;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/samsung-galaxy-z-fold-4-review-specs-price-a-flagship-foldable-refined-131543810.html"><strong>阅读我们对三星 Galaxy Z Fold 4 的完整评论</strong></a></p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/best-android-phone-130030805.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/best-android-phone-130030805.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 8de89a2d-b344-4d22-ae89-b314b75fcb1d</guid><dc:creator>萨姆·卢瑟福</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Thu, 06 Jul 2023 17:28:19 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1688664500</ingested><modified> 2023-07-06T17:28:33+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Consumer Discretionary]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[Handheld & Connected Devices]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Sam Rutherford]]></category><media:content height="1200" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-03/78c254a0-bd23-11ed-bb1f-7eca272d4986" width="2000"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1200" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-03/cadc65a0-bd23-11ed-baff-10789780782f" width="2000"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Sam Rutherford/Engadget]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Here's a photo of our favorite Android phones on the market right now featuring the Google Pixel 7, Pixel 7 Pro, Pixel 6a, Samsung Galaxy S23 Ultra, Samsung Galaxy Z Fold 4 and the OnePlus 11.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[The best Android phones you can buy right now]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Simogo tries to explain the mysteries of ‘Lorelei and the Laser Eyes’]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>一般来说，游戏创建过程从机制开始。开发人员往往想要探索一种输入方法，甚至可能有一个他们认为在交互式环境中特别强大的故事情节。通常有一个以“第一人称射击游戏”或“等距 Roguelike”等类型为基础的中心主题，游戏在这个框架内汇集在一起​​，其细节和专有名词在此过程中逐渐具体化。</p><p>在<em>罗蕾莱和激光眼</em>的例子中，西莫戈从这个名字开始。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> “没有任何一个<em>恍然大悟的</em>时刻，”Simogo 联合创始人西蒙·弗莱瑟 (Simon Flesser) 告诉 Engadget。 “我们有了自己真正喜欢的标题，从那里我们一直试图弄清楚激光眼是什么。” </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/2de91e01-1c14-11ee-a3dc-fc969b6bdc46" style="height:1080px;width:1920px;" alt="罗蕾莱和激光眼" data-uuid="66a747f3-f29e-3b28-96d8-e42636916511"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">西莫戈</div></figure><p><em>《Lorelei and the Laser Eyes》</em>是 Simogo 的第九款主要游戏，Simogo 是一家广受好评的瑞典工作室，曾制作过<em>《Device 6》</em> 、 <em>《Year Walk》</em>和<em>《Sayonara Wild Hearts》</em> 。 <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/nintendo-direct-lorelei-and-the-laser-eyes-simogo-sayonara-wild-hearts-annapurna-interactive-161543878.html">西莫戈揭示了<em>罗蕾莱</em></a><em>&nbsp;</em> 2022 年 6 月，一部黑色风格的预告片讲述了一个谋杀之谜、一个充满欺骗的迷宫和一座记忆的宫殿。一名衣着考究的女士在预告片文字后面懒洋洋地走动，在一座大庄园的单色场地中穿行时，她的眼睛泛着红光。</p><p> Simogo 在首次亮相时并没有透露有关<em>Lorelei 的</em>大量细节，此后也没有提供太多清晰的信息。该游戏的最新预告片涵盖了 1847 年、1963 年和 2014 年，暗示了具有超自然现象的国际间谍活动，强调了玩家识别模式和解决谜题的能力。 “你还记得那个迷宫吗？”预告片一遍又一遍地问。</p><p>因此，以下是直接来自 Flesser 的有关<em>Lorelei 和激光眼</em>的一些基本细节：</p><ul><li><p>这是一款第三人称解谜冒险游戏。</p></li><li><p>它是非线性的。</p></li><li><p>有近 150 个谜题需要解决。</p></li><li><p>它即将登陆 PC 和 Switch。</p></li><li><p>它以“一座房子的超现实记忆”为背景。</p></li></ul><p></p><p> <em>Lorelei and the Laser Eyes</em>在 3D 空间中使用摄像机，借鉴<em>《Sayonara Wild Hearts》</em>中的最佳创意，并通过不断变化的机制和视角。这感觉很神秘，因为，嗯，就是这样。</p><p> “该项目的制作具有变革性，这反映在它的主题中，”弗莱瑟说。 “这不是一个单一的概念，而是长期以来想法的集合。从主题上讲，有很多关于故事中的故事、相互反映的故事、记忆、梦想以及平行事件和世界的想法。” </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/2de91e00-1c14-11ee-b6a8-d4c1ad910c51" style="height:1080px;width:1920px;" alt="罗蕾莱和激光眼" data-uuid="93167572-54d0-3f5d-bb59-4907af9d6d0f"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">西莫戈</div></figure><p>玩家将与相机、电脑和锁等物体进行交互；他们会阅读书籍和杂志中的段落；弗莱瑟表示，他们会在游戏中玩游戏。</p><p> “我们正在努力灌输一种感觉，事情并不像看上去那样，”他说。 “不是恐惧，而是一种持续的矛盾心理，一个没有善恶之分的故事。还有一种荒谬感——发现自己处于一种奇怪的境地，你最终会开始质疑正在发生什么、没有发生什么。”</p><p>基本上，西莫戈想要扰乱你的思想。这就是该工作室的一大成果——它之前的游戏<em>《Year Walk》</em> 、 <em>《The Sailor&#39;s Dream》</em>和<em>《Device 6》</em>都成功地玩弄了超现实主义和超自然事件。</p><p> “我认为当你开始融合现实时，会发生一些有趣的事情，”弗莱瑟说。 “当[一段]媒体开始谈论我们的现实，就好像它是现实中的一个故事一样，它最终会以某种方式变得更加真实。它以一种非常具体的方式潜入你的脑海。你就成为了故事。” </p><div id="1060e81182514bf7a5bb590359614775"><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/-MzDNtYCy0o?rel=0" style="top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;position:absolute;border:0;" allowfullscreen="" scrolling="no"></iframe></div><p> <em>《Lorelei and the Laser Eyes》</em>尚无发布日期，但由 Annapurna Interactive 发行，预计将于 2024 年在 PC 和 Switch 上发布。该游戏的第二个预告片于上周发布：最后，一系列迷宫块在屏幕上闪过，它们的位置就好像句子中的单词一样。这感觉就像是一个挑战，或者也许是一个邀请，去解决罗蕾莱的一个谜题。感觉游戏已经开始了。</p><p> Steam 上至少有一个人声称他们已经将迷宫块转化为完整的想法，并且他们的结果似乎很合适（对于那些好奇的人， <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://steamcommunity.com/app/2008920/discussions/0/3809531058949238993/">请在此处链接</a>）。我向弗莱瑟询问了神秘方块的正确翻译，但他没有提供。相反，他简单地说：“一切都是一个谜。”</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/simogo-tries-to-explain-the-mysteries-of-lorelei-and-the-laser-eyes-161941692.html?src=rss]] >; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/simogo-tries-to-explain-the-mysteries-of-lorelei-and-the-laser-eyes-161941692.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 04ad39b1-edd0-4734-9d48-827098776076</guid><dc:creator>杰西卡·康迪特</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Thu, 06 Jul 2023 16:19:41 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1688661993</ingested><modified> 2023-07-06T16:46:38+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Consumer Discretionary]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Jessica Conditt]]></category><media:content height="1080" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/703afc80-1c1c-11ee-b7e7-db2da03bc705" width="1920"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1080" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/703afc80-1c1c-11ee-b7e7-db2da03bc705" width="1920"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Simogo]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[A scene from the video game 'Lorelei and the Laser Eyes' showing a woman in the foreground with a glowing eye(s) -- seen from slightly behind -- and a fancy dinner table with two diners at opposite ends with a candelabra in between them. The surrounding room is faded, dark and highlighted by a subtle red glow.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Lorelei and the Laser Eyes]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[The best gaming laptops for 2023]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>几年来，游戏笔记本电脑一直是最有趣的电脑之一。它们自然变得更薄、更轻，但它们也变得更加强大和高效，使它们适合工作和娱乐。他们采用了一些大胆的创新，例如旋转铰链和接近桌面的可定制性。游戏笔记本电脑是个人电脑制造商可以大胆尝试的领域。</p><p>如果您是市场上购买功能强大的新电脑的专业人士，并且您喜欢偶尔玩几轮《Apex Legends》，那么购买游戏笔记本电脑而不是类似 MacBook Pro 的工作站可能更有意义。您仍然可以获得充足的视频编码和 3D 渲染功能，而且您最终可能会花费更少。我们将帮助您找出最适合您的游戏笔记本电脑，从戴尔 G15 等经济型笔记本电脑到 Razer Blade 15 等高端笔记本电脑以及介于两者之间的所有产品。 </p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2020-08/1c6ceae0-e935-11ea-9d63-fcfd47b39fd9" alt="华硕 ROG G14" data-uuid="c9c32383-a076-3311-b097-70654cf5e3c1"><figcaption>德文德拉·哈达瓦/Engadget</figcaption></figure><h2><br>您的预算是多少？</h2><p>您的笔记本电脑购买之旅的开始和结束取决于您愿意花费的金额。这并不奇怪。好消息：对于各种预算的游戏玩家来说，都有很多选择。特别是，我们看到了一些 1,000 美元以下的入门级 PC 游戏选择，例如戴尔的 G15 系列。这个价格范围内的廉价游戏笔记本电脑肯定会比价格更高的型号感觉更脆弱，而且它们可能会在 RAM、存储和整体功率上有所减少。 But most budget gaming laptops should be able to handle the majority of video games running at 1080p at 60 frames per second, which is the bare minimum you&#39;d want from any system.</p><p> Things get interesting when you start looking at the best gaming laptops in the mid-range space, with prices at $1,000 and higher. At that point, you&#39;ll start finding PCs like the <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/asus-zephyrus-g14-review-amd-ryzen-radeon-173016459.html">ASUS Zephyrus ROG G14</a> , one of our favorite gaming notebooks. In general, you can look forward to far better build quality than budget laptops (metal cases!), improved graphics power and enough RAM and storage space to handle the most demanding games. These are the gaming machines we&#39;d recommend for most people, as they&#39;ll keep you gaming and working for years before you need to worry about an upgrade.</p><p> If you&#39;re willing to spend around $1,800 or more, you can start considering more premium options like Razer&#39;s Blade. Expect impeccably polished cases, the fastest hardware on the market, and ridiculously thin designs. The sky&#39;s the limit here: Alienware&#39;s uber customizable Area 51m is an enormous beast that can cost up to $4,700. Few people need a machine that high-end, but if you&#39;re a gamer with extra cash to burn, it may be worth taking a close look at some of these pricier systems. </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2020-08/a3e1f580-e933-11ea-bf65-73681726b0ba" alt="Origin Evo16" data-uuid="4a48e7b5-427c-3293-87a2-1f30ac1128e6"><figcaption></figcaption></figure><h2><br> What kind of CPU and GPU do you want?</h2><p> The answer to this question used to be relatively simple: Just get an Intel chip with an NVIDIA GPU. But over the last few years AMD has stepped up its game with its Ryzen notebook processors, which are better suited for juggling multiple tasks at once (like streaming to Twitch while blasting fools in Fortnite). Intel responded with its impressive 12th and 13th-gen chips, but it&#39;s nice to have decent Ryzen AMD alternatives available, especially since they&#39;re often cheaper than comparable Intel models.</p><p> When it comes to video cards, though, AMD is still catching up. Its Radeon RX 6000M GPU has been a fantastic performer in notebooks like <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/asus-rog-strix-g15-advantage-review-amd-radeon-rx-6000m-120031416.html">ASUS&#39;s ROG Strix G15</a> , but it lags behind NVIDIA when it comes to newer features like ray tracing. (We&#39;re still waiting to test AMD&#39;s new Radeon 7000 series mobile graphics.) At the very least, a Radeon-powered notebook can approach the general gaming performance of the NVIDIA RTX 3070 and 3080 GPUs.</p><p> If you want to future-proof your purchase, or you&#39;re just eager to see how much better ray tracing can make your games look, you&#39;re probably better off with an NVIDIA video card. They&#39;re in far more systems, and it&#39;s clear that they have better optimized ray tracing technology. NVIDIA GeForce RTX GPUs also feature the company&#39;s DLSS technology, which uses AI to upscale games to higher resolutions. That&#39;ll let you play a game like <em>Destiny 2</em> in 4K with faster frame rates. That&#39;s useful if you&#39;re trying to take advantage of a high refresh rate monitor.</p><p> You&#39;ll still find plenty of laptops with NVIDIA&#39;s older RTX 30-series GPUs these days, and they&#39;ll still give you tremendous performance. But to be safe, it&#39;s probably worth opting for the newer RTX 40-series systems, since they support the newer DLSS 3 technology and offer a wealth of performance upgrades. (If you&#39;re looking out for the best deals, you can probably find some killer RTX 3070 laptops out there.) The entry-level RTX 4050 is a solid start, but we&#39;d suggest going for a 4060 or 4070 if you&#39;re aiming to maximize your framerates on faster screens. The RTX 4080 and 4090 are both incredibly powerful, but they typically make systems far too expensive for most users.</p><p> It&#39;s worth noting that NVIDIA&#39;s mobile GPUs aren&#39;t directly comparable to its more powerful desktop hardware. PC makers can also tweak voltages to make gaming performance better in a thinner case. Basically, don&#39;t be surprised if you see notebooks that perform very differently, even if they&#39;re all equipped with the same GPU. </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2020-08/22960650-e934-11ea-92de-9913d49e86b1" alt="雷蛇灵刃 15" data-uuid="4f9811ff-53fe-37d3-bd55-dbe2ef195155"><figcaption></figcaption></figure><h2><br> What kind of screen do you want?</h2><p> Screen size is a good place to start when judging gaming notebooks. In general, 15-inch laptops will be the best balance of immersion and portability, while larger 17-inch models are heftier, but naturally give you more screen real estate. There are some 13-inch gaming notebooks, like the Razer Blade Stealth, but paradoxically you&#39;ll often end up paying more for those than slightly larger 15-inch options. We&#39;re also seeing plenty of 14-inch options, like the Zephyrus G14 and Blade 14, which are generally beefier than 13-inch laptops while still being relatively portable.</p><p> But these days, there is plenty to consider beyond screen size. For one: refresh rates. Most monitors refresh their screens vertically 60 times per second, or at 60Hz. That&#39;s a standard in use since black and white NTSC TVs. But over the past few years, displays have evolved considerably. Now, 120Hz 1080p screens are the bare minimum you&#39;d want in any gaming notebook — and there are faster 144Hz, 240Hz and even 360Hz panels. All of this is in the service of one thing: making everything on your display look as smooth as possible.</p><p> For games, higher refresh rates also help eliminate screen tearing and other artifacts that could get in the way of your frag fest. And for everything else, it just leads to a better viewing experience. Even scrolling a web page on a 120Hz or faster monitor is starkly different from a 60Hz screen. Instead of seeing a jittery wall of text and pictures, everything moves seamlessly, as if you&#39;re unwinding a glossy paper magazine. Going beyond 120Hz makes gameplay look even more responsive, which to some players gives them a slight advantage. </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2020-08/821d1030-e936-11ea-9d7f-aed162772f3d" alt="Gigabyte Aero 15" data-uuid="5bf22bf9-dcbe-3c68-8aee-ccf82ff50f7b"><figcaption> Steve Dent/Engadget</figcaption></figure><p> Not to make things more complicated, but you should also keep an eye out for NVIDIA&#39;s G-SYNC and AMD&#39;s FreeSync. They&#39;re both adaptive sync technologies that can match your screen&#39;s refresh rate with the framerate of your game. That also helps to reduce screen tearing and make gameplay smoother. Consider them nice bonuses on top of a high refresh rate monitor; they&#39;re not necessary, but they can still offer a slight visual improvement.</p><p><strong>也可以看看：</strong></p><ul><li><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-laptops-120008636.html"><strong>2023 年最佳笔记本电脑</strong></a></p></li><li><p><a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-affordable-windows-laptops-123000512.html"><strong>最便宜的 Windows 笔记本电脑</strong></a></p></li><li><p><a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-2-in-1-laptops-173038508.html"><strong>2023 年最佳二合一笔记本电脑</strong></a></p></li><li><p><a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-chromebooks-160054646.html"><strong>最好的 Chromebook</strong></a></p></li><li><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-laptops-for-students-130054631.html"><strong>最适合大学生的笔记本电脑</strong></a></p></li></ul><p>One more thing: Most of these suggestions are related to LCD screens, not OLEDs. While OLED makes a phenomenal choice for TVs, it&#39;s a bit more complicated when it comes to gaming laptops. They&#39;re mostly limited to 60Hz, though some models offer 90Hz. Still, you won&#39;t see the smoothness of a 120Hz or 144Hz screen. OLEDs also typically come as 4K or 3.5K panels – you&#39;ll need a ton of GPU power to run games natively at that resolution. They look incredible, with the best black levels and contrast on the market, but we think most gamers would be better off with an LCD. </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2020-08/7a4d3480-e935-11ea-9ffa-4c77ce132136" alt="ASUS ROG G14" data-uuid="4bbe8bbe-f37d-3ae2-9ca5-2fcf2d064b79"><figcaption> Devindra Hardawar/Engadget</figcaption></figure><h3><br> A few other takeaways:</h3><ul><li><p> Get at least 16GB of RAM. And if you&#39;re planning to do a ton of multitasking while streaming, 32GB is worth considering.</p></li><li><p> Storage is still a huge concern. These days, I&#39;d recommend aiming for a 1TB M.2 SSD, which should be enough space to juggle a few large titles like Destiny 2. (If you can afford the jump to a 2TB SSD though, just do it.) Some laptops also have room for standard SATA drives, which are far cheaper than M.2&#39;s and can hold more data.</p></li><li><p> Get your hands on a system before you buy it. I&#39;d recommend snagging the best gaming laptop for you from a retailer with a simple return policy, like Amazon or Best Buy. If you don&#39;t like it, you can always ship it back easily.</p></li><li><p> Don&#39;t forget about accessories! For the best performance, you&#39;ll need <a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2018-03-16-the-best-gaming-mouse.html">a good mouse</a> , <a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2018-12-06-how-to-buy-gaming-keyboard-2018.html">keyboard</a> and <a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2019-09-16-how-to-buy-a-gaming-headset.html">headphones</a> .<br></p></li></ul><h2> Best overall: ASUS ROG Zephyrus G14</h2><p><core-commerce id="c61b76c3a3304401935acc6f47b1989c" data-type="product-list"></p><p> If you can&#39;t tell by now, we really like the <a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9ncC9wcm9kdWN0L0IwODhQREI2M1o_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8tYXQtMjAiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjQzNjJhYWI0LTgwOGUtMzM5ZC05NmNkLTcwMTg5MWQ1NzAwMCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAVdU3ljcyMunRp3l1YUqc8x7MVN4kZk4MbsSfWC8F31R&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fgp%2Fproduct%2FB088PDB63Z">Zephyrus G14</a> . It&#39;s shockingly compact, at just 3.5 pounds, and features AMD&#39;s new Ryzen chips paired together with its Radeon 6000M graphics (we&#39;d recommend the Ryzen 9 model with an RX 6700M for $1,400). While its 14-inch screen is a bit smaller than our other recommendations, it looks great and features a fast 144Hz refresh rate. We also like its retro-future design (some configurations have tiny LEDs on its rear panel for extra flair). While the <a data-i13n="cpos:12;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/asus-zephyrus-g14-review-190037967.html">G14</a> has jumped in price since it debuted, it&#39;s still one of the best gaming notebooks around, especially since ASUS has finally added a built-in webcam.</p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:13;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/asus-zephyrus-g14-review-amd-ryzen-radeon-173016459.html"><strong>Read our Full Review of ASUS ROG Zephyrus G14</strong></a></p><h2> Best budget: Dell G15</h2><p><core-commerce id="d0fbcfc300994f6bae7bda8088cff01b" data-type="product-list"></p><p> We&#39;ve been fans of Dell&#39;s G5 line ever since it first appeared a few years ago. Now dubbed the <a data-i13n="cpos:14;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAQDQavbARvn12lh8gWWj9FABnXmHlI8rlZ5QPlPndIE1&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FDell-G15-5520-Gaming-Laptop%2Fdp%2FB09WQBS587">G15</a> , it starts at under $1,000 and, while not the most powerful gaming laptop, it features all of the latest hardware, like Intel&#39;s 13th-generation CPUs and NVIDIA&#39;s RTX 40-series cards. (You can also find <a data-i13n="cpos:15;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/alienware-m15-dell-g15-amd-ryzen-cpu-130014937.html">AMD Ryzen chips</a> in some models.) This budget-friendly gaming laptop is a bit heavy, weighing over five pounds, but it&#39;s a solid notebook otherwise. And you can even bring it into mid-range gaming territory if you spec up to the RTX 4060.</p><h2> Best premium gaming laptop: Razer Blade 15</h2><p><core-commerce id="5a9394fa7ebe47999cf5786abfba648d" data-type="product-list"></p><p> Razer continues to do a stellar job of delivering bleeding-edge hardware in a sleek package that would make Mac users jealous. The <a data-i13n="cpos:16;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9SYXplci1CbGFkZS1HYW1pbmctTGFwdG9wLVRodW5kZXJib2x0L2RwL0IwOVJCSkM4WTk_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8tYXQtMjAiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjQzNjJhYWI0LTgwOGUtMzM5ZC05NmNkLTcwMTg5MWQ1NzAwMCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAeEZ03GyGAvrKUobmJH32FlbeBVQkYjxHEHfZUOlsJ_7&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FRazer-Blade-Gaming-Laptop-Thunderbolt%2Fdp%2FB09RBJC8Y9">Blade 15</a> has just about everything you&#39;d want for great gaming, including NVIDIA&#39;s RTX 4080, Intel&#39;s 13th-gen CPUs and speedy quad-HD screens. Our recommendation? Consider the model with a Quad HD 165Hz screen and an RTX 4060 GPU for $2,500. You can easily save some cash by going for a cheaper notebook, but they won&#39;t feel nearly as polished as the Blade.</p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:17;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/razer-blade-15-2022-review-a-real-treat-if-youve-got-the-cash-160032467.html"><strong>阅读我们对 Razer Blade 15 的完整评测</strong></a></p><h2>Another good option: Acer Predator Triton 500 SE</h2><p><core-commerce id="170ad31f49834bfaa4dc9a7f7641ad08" data-type="product-list"></p><p> While we&#39;ve seen some wilder concepts from Acer, like its 360-degree hinge-equipped Triton 900, the <a data-i13n="cpos:18;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAUw0BXEzBSg9fFaoSxlDlV756duKUnNYi51vCnRdO0Fc&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fgp%2Fproduct%2FB09TBPWQ34%2F">Triton 500</a> is a more affordable bread and butter option. This year, it&#39;s bumped up to a 16-inch display, giving you more of an immersive gaming experience. It&#39;s relatively thin, weighs just over five pounds, and it can be equipped with Intel&#39;s 11th-gen CPUs and NVIDIA&#39;s RTX 30-series GPUs. Acer&#39;s build quality is as sturdy as ever, and it has most of the standard features you&#39;d need in a gaming notebook.</p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:19;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/acer-predator-triton-500-se-review-183526914.html"><strong>Read our Full Review of Acer Predator Triton 500 SE Gaming Laptop</strong></a></p><h2> Best large gaming laptop: Alienware m18</h2><p><core-commerce id="8cbd2913156c47548c3e8a8d8032af2c" data-type="product-list"></p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:20;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Dell;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=b1bb23c9-a2d4-4e4e-bfac-7a560ebe7641&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Dell&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAVi0W8PfHT6q8wJVAernCYX9T4nFwo1u5yWeNCWMf3Cc&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dell.com%2Fen-us%2Fshop%2Fgaming-laptops%2Falienware-m18-gaming-laptop%2Fspd%2Falienware-m18-r1-laptop">Alienware&#39;s m18</a> is its biggest gaming laptop ever, and it packs in just about everything we&#39;d want. It can be equipped with Intel and AMD&#39;s fastest CPUs, as well as NVIDIA&#39;s fastest GPUs (including the 4090). Its base configuration with an RTX 4060 is also surprisingly affordable for an 18-inch laptop, starting at $2,100. We&#39;ve always liked Alienware&#39;s m-series gaming laptops, but this year they&#39;re more refined, with better cooling and a slightly sleeker design. You can also opt for CherryMX mechanical keys, which deliver a desktop-like gaming and typing experience.</p><h2> Best with a dual screen: ASUS ROG Zephyrus Duo 16</h2><p><core-commerce id="b0532de86cd540c1a1683bc7a8e94745" data-type="product-list"></p><p></p><p>You know if you actually need a dual-screen laptop: Maybe a single 17-inch screen isn&#39;t enough, or you want a mobile setup that&#39;s closer to a multi-monitor desktop. If that&#39;s the case, the <a data-i13n="cpos:21;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAdmL5ixpdITYH7C1PwkWNPOzJOOGww3IiHZHQWMD3zTj&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fgp%2Fproduct%2FB09YN6PTYM%2F">Zephyrus Duo 16</a> is the best laptop for you. It&#39;s powerful, and its extra 14-inch screen can easily let you multitask while<del> gaming</del> dutifully working. It also has all of the latest hardware you&#39;d want, like AMD&#39;s new Ryzen chips and NVIDIA&#39;s RTX 4000 GPUs. Sure, it&#39;s nowhere near portable, but a true multitasker won&#39;t mind.</p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:22;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/asus-rog-zephyrus-duo-16-review-when-two-screens-are-better-than-one-specs-price-120018789.html"><strong>Read our Full Review of ASUS ROG Zephyrus Duo 16 Gaming Laptop</strong></a></p><p></p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/best-gaming-laptops-172033838.html?src=rss]]>;</description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/best-gaming-laptops-172033838.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 4362aab4-808e-339d-96cd-701891d57000</guid><dc:creator> Devindra Hardawar</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher> Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Thu, 06 Jul 2023 13:56:03 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1688651763</ingested><modified> 2023-07-06T13:56:13+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[news]]></category><category><![CDATA[Dell]]></category><category><![CDATA[gaming]]></category><category><![CDATA[PredatorTriton500]]></category><category><![CDATA[Alienware]]></category><category><![CDATA[thebuyersguide]]></category><category><![CDATA[Razer]]></category><category><![CDATA[commerce]]></category><category><![CDATA[Blade]]></category><category><![CDATA[ASUS]]></category><category><![CDATA[Acer]]></category><category><![CDATA[ROGZephyrusG14]]></category><category><![CDATA[G515]]></category><category><![CDATA[gaminglaptops]]></category><category><![CDATA[gear]]></category><category><![CDATA[ElectronicEquipment,Instruments&Components]]></category><category><![CDATA[VideoGames]]></category><category><![CDATA[ElectronicsAccessories]]></category><category><![CDATA[MobileApps]]></category><category><![CDATA[OfficeElectronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology&Electronics]]></category><category><![CDAT